<item>
            <title>[HBASE-8988] Reuse the thread pool in the shell to not run out of threads</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-8988</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I was trying some stuff in the shell and tried just to get a few puts in a loop to a table. I quickly ran out of threads (java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: unable to create new native thread).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It seems we create a new HTable per get/put/etc call. We could just reuse one thread pool instead.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
